China (Shandong), Japan: Honshu. The host plant 
Vitis amurensis
is widespread in the northeast and eastern parts of China (
Chen et al. 2007
), Eastern Russia (
Afonin et al. 2008
), Japan: Honshu and Korea (
Ohwi 1965
). A much wider distribution of the moth is expected, where its host plants occur.
